mdes.slick.sui
Class Sui

java.lang.Object
  mdes.slick.sui.Sui
public class Sui
extends java.lang.Object

Sui is a utility class for the GUI library. It should be used for initializing the system and changing global settings.

The skin is first installed when one of the init() methods is called.

updateComponentTreeSkin

public static void updateComponentTreeSkin(Component comp)
Updates the current skin/theme, asking each node in the given tree to update their appearance by calling:
comp.updateAppearance()

This will install the "skin default" appearance on the tree. If this is undesired, it is suggested that you use updateComponentTreeTheme, which will re-install the currently set appearance.

updateComponentTreeTheme

public static void updateComponentTreeTheme(Component comp)
Updates the current theme, asking each node in the given tree to update their appearance by calling:
comp.setAppearance(comp.getAppearance());

setSkin

public static void setSkin(Skin s)
                    throws org.newdawn.slick.SlickException
Sets the current skin which components use for rendering. When a new skin is set, the old skin is uninstalled. The passed skin will be installed to initialize resources. Most skins will "cache" their resources to make installation fast.

Parameters:
s - the new skin to set
Throws:
org.newdawn.slick.SlickException - if there was a problem uninstalling the old skin or reinstalling the new skin
